#### On Self-Hosted GPU Privacy:
> "Because LedgerX processes highly sensitive transaction logs and digital signatures, I designed a privacy-first AI layer by self-hosting Llama-3-8B-Instruct on serverless GPU infrastructure. This kept all financial ledger data completely secure and off of third-party public AI APIs."

#### On Prompt Security:
> "To protect the ledger database from prompt injections, I implemented a zero-trust prompt architecture. The LLM is strictly sandbox-confined, inputs are vetted through guardrails, and the AI cannot write directly to MongoDB—it only drafts structural adjustments that merchants must manually sign off on."
